Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.54,0:00:11.61,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Chiranosuke's Code, number one:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.13,0:00:15.56,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You must not change history \Nwithout my permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.21,0:00:17.42,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Number two:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.42,0:00:20.24,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You must not tell anyone else the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.12,0:00:23.29,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll make it easy to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.00,0:00:26.71,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}First, this is the world you're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.71,0:00:30.96,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And this train travels down \Nthe rail, toward the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.96,0:00:34.17,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If it goes straight, it will arrive here, \Nat the worst-case scenario,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.17,0:00:36.51,Punchline-Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the New Year's Eve when the asteroid hits.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.31,0:00:38.72,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I need you to go
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.72,0:00:42.56,Punchline-Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}toward the New Year's Eve \Nwhere the asteroid doesn't strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.06,0:00:47.73,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Beyond that is a supremely \Nhappy and peaceful future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.98,0:00:50.53,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To guide the world to that future is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.53,0:00:54.99,Punchline-Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the ultimate purpose of the \NHuman Preservation Project.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.61,0:01:02.20,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In any case, you absolutely, unfailingly, \Nmust succeed in this project.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.76,0:01:05.60,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That is your destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.90,0:01:09.64,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I'll tell you this:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.18,0:01:12.35,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}there is no "next" for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.45,0:01:23.07,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.07,0:01:25.42,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Two days with no progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.85,0:01:35.89,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ito, open up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.89,0:01:37.32,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,What was that noise just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.55,0:01:41.20,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,That was, uh... It was me. I screamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.20,0:01:42.45,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.24,0:01:47.74,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, I remember this happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.28,0:01:49.21,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,To Yu-tan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:52.92,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,I found something funny here,\Nso I'm sending it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.92,0:01:54.96,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,They were selling it at a party store.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.27,0:01:57.47,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? Isn't it hilarious?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.87,0:02:02.01,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, do you remember how \Nthe poem "Ame ni mo makezu" goes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.50,0:02:07.33,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,I think we learned it in school, \Nbut I didn't remember it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.02,0:02:11.46,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,So I looked it up online,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.46,0:02:16.42,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,and when I read it again, I just loved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.29,0:02:18.61,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,You should read it, too, Yu-tan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.53,0:02:22.43,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,Losing neither to rain, nor the wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.43,0:02:25.10,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,losing neither to the snow, \Nnor to the heat of summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.10,0:02:30.00,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,Having a strong body, unfettered by desire, \Nand never offending anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.87,0:02:41.33,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Like I could wear this thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.98,0:03:00.23,Punchline-Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Punch Line
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.04,0:04:23.03,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.41,0:04:29.50,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Super helper-man of justice, \NMiyazawa Kenji, is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.07,0:04:32.11,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Miyazawa Kenji?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.54,0:04:35.62,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,Another freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.05,0:04:41.19,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,What, aren't you going to attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.19,0:04:43.28,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,But I know I'm going to lose...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.28,0:04:44.11,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.11,0:04:45.63,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.98,0:04:48.62,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, then I'll start—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.62,0:04:51.48,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! I'm not emotionally prepared!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.78,0:04:54.94,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,Called a nobody by everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.28,0:04:58.06,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,Never praised, never blamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.82,0:05:01.07,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Akina,0000,0000,0000,,That's the kind of person I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.39,0:05:09.24,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,...want to become.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.24,0:05:10.01,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.34,0:05:12.24,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I decided I'd become that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.24,0:05:16.75,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,so I could guide this world to a supremely \Nhappy and peaceful future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.98,0:05:19.13,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.44,0:05:21.75,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Just give me twenty seconds, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.75,0:05:23.14,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,What if I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.14,0:05:24.63,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Do I get a reward?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.63,0:05:27.38,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'll amply reward you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.26,0:05:29.27,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.27,0:05:30.18,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Nineteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.18,0:05:30.98,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Eighteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:32.21,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.45,0:05:36.80,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I knew I'd come here, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.80,0:05:41.10,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know who's there, \Nbut can you get this off of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.10,0:05:42.86,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.51,0:05:45.57,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.17,0:06:01.50,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, time out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.50,0:06:02.42,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Don't run!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.75,0:06:06.85,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,Muhi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.33,0:06:10.95,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,As promised, your reward—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.95,0:06:11.76,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.27,0:06:13.69,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,That bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.69,0:06:16.14,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.92,0:06:18.35,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,He's like...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.35,0:06:20.79,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,A totally different person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.27,0:06:26.40,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Should I be chasing him like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.66,0:06:29.23,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Chiranosuke's Code, number one:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.23,0:06:32.99,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,You must not change history \Nwithout my permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.39,0:06:36.98,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,So far, six billion, three hundred \Nseventy-three million,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.98,0:06:40.14,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,one hundred fifty-three thousand, \Nseven hundred forty yous
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.14,0:06:43.04,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,have broken that code, and went on to fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.92,0:06:50.93,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I can't just let him get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:53.01,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that hurt, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:54.60,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Does it really matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.60,0:06:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not even your body, Tsubouchi Qmay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.41,0:07:00.56,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.87,0:07:02.86,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter who I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.86,0:07:06.07,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Why is Asteroid VR-1 hitting Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.07,0:07:08.36,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:09.57,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.15,0:07:19.62,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,We have no intention of \Nbringing down the asteroid...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.62,0:07:21.00,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.45,0:07:23.63,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Because W isn't complete yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.84,0:07:30.01,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Right. That cub's regenerative ability \Nis imperative to W's completion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.28,0:07:33.06,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it belonged to the\NQmay Group to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.06,0:07:34.91,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Who told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.91,0:07:36.35,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Does it matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:39.95,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that we created it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.30,0:07:41.69,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,At Uber Labs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.69,0:07:43.10,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Uber Labs?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.31,0:07:45.03,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,So you have heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.43,0:07:48.86,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,You appear to be a Uberfier too, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:52.36,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying the lab was \Na Qmay Group facility?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.36,0:07:54.02,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.02,0:07:58.85,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,The Uberfication predictions, \Nthe Hercules virus design...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.85,0:08:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all my doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.25,0:08:02.79,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to us is all your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.47,0:08:07.17,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think there'd be any \Npoint in hurting this body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.17,0:08:08.98,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.41,0:08:13.80,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,You'd never understand \Nmy sublime philosophies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.48,0:08:17.97,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity must evolve into a perfect form.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.32,0:08:22.76,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,That's the only way to \Nbring about world peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.55,0:08:26.53,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I created the Qmay Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.95,0:08:30.89,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,When I presented the people with the \Nmiraculous power of Uberfication,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.89,0:08:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the fools followed me with gleaming eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.98,0:08:39.82,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,The people want that power.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.82,0:08:41.00,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,You're insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.25,0:08:44.75,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, evolution is beyond the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.45,0:08:48.48,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,You've already taken the first step.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.81,0:08:49.84,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.58,0:08:53.51,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you come work for us again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.51,0:08:54.88,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.23,0:08:57.53,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,You'll soon understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.53,0:09:00.41,Default,Kameotoko,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be waiting for your return.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.40,0:09:26.25,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,But to think you were Strange Juice, Mikatan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.38,0:09:32.17,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't scare me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.17,0:09:35.42,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that man was back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.01,0:09:38.06,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably at the hospital by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.56,0:09:40.51,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,He was taken in an ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.01,0:09:43.42,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Narugino, you don't have to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.82,0:09:45.52,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,I know who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.55,0:09:47.52,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.52,0:09:49.62,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,Just who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.14,0:09:51.46,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't I told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.46,0:09:56.25,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the super helper-man of \Njustice, Miyazawa Kenji!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.09,0:10:02.53,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, I have nothing to do with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.53,0:10:05.29,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Meika, can I talk to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.82,0:10:08.17,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.49,0:10:14.63,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,And what do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.63,0:10:17.34,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd help you with the repairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.61,0:10:19.43,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,R-Repairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.43,0:10:24.14,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Your fusion reactor broke \Ndown after that man hit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.14,0:10:25.14,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.14,0:10:27.18,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? W-Wait—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.14,0:10:30.15,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.67,0:10:37.74,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, how did you know I was a robot?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.20,0:10:40.81,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,In a word, destiny, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.66,0:10:43.11,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Destiny, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.51,0:10:45.16,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Fair enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.06,0:10:47.20,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.20,0:10:48.96,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.96,0:10:51.18,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't it bother you a little more?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.48,0:10:54.47,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'd be lying if I \Nsaid it didn't bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.47,0:10:57.97,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,But I trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.19,0:10:59.34,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,You trust me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.96,0:11:02.85,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa told me about you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.19,0:11:05.43,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,a long time ago, before he passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.87,0:11:09.85,Punchline-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Meika,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.70,0:11:13.38,Punchline-Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,it seems my time's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.38,0:11:14.36,Punchline-Flashback,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.61,0:11:16.41,Punchline-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cry, Meika.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.81,0:11:19.86,Punchline-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.69,0:11:25.87,Punchline-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,You remember my three last requests, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.70,0:11:34.38,Punchline-Flashback,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,First, protect a girl named Chiyoko, \Nand raise her to be a good hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.85,0:11:40.38,Punchline-Flashback,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Second, create a secret organization, \NJustice Punch, with Chiyoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.38,0:11:42.00,Punchline-Flashback,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,And third...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.44,0:11:45.28,Punchline-Flashback,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Grandpa?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.56,0:11:48.10,Punchline-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Meika.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.52,0:11:52.66,Punchline-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Justice Punch will one day save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.13,0:11:55.11,Punchline-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,That's the will of the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.72,0:11:58.87,Punchline-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ever...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.63,0:12:03.81,Punchline-Flashback,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.70,0:12:06.99,Punchline-Flashback,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.51,0:12:10.17,Punchline-Flashback,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.54,0:12:14.67,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's the third?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.67,0:12:15.32,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:17.54,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,What's the third request?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.87,0:12:23.05,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,"A hero in a creepy costume will \None day appear before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.23,0:12:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trust him. He's not a bad person."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.32,0:12:29.33,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Creepy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.33,0:12:32.93,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,And apparently, he's a member \Nof Justice Punch, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.44,0:12:34.31,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.99,0:12:36.31,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Just two more.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.31,0:12:39.64,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,The "Punch" in "Justice Punch" comes \Nfrom "pan̄ja," meaning "five" in Hindi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.64,0:12:42.32,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it's a group \Nof five heroes of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.32,0:12:44.82,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Then the other two are...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.45,0:12:47.52,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.52,0:12:49.74,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, repairs done.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.94,0:12:52.29,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.29,0:12:56.04,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, how did Professor Tenga \Nknow about the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.29,0:13:00.55,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,This is called a Reizoukou.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.11,0:13:03.79,Punchline-Summary,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(501,1)}Underworld Graphic Communicator
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.11,0:13:03.79,Punchline-Reizoukou,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(501,1)}rei                          zou   kou
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.29,0:13:03.80,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}It stands for Underworld \NGraphic Communicator.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.51,0:13:06.39,Default,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a fax machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.39,0:13:08.39,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know too much about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.75,0:13:13.64,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,But he said that one day, he got a \Nfax message about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.88,0:13:16.15,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,A fax?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.49,0:13:19.20,Punchline-Flashback,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...writing down diagrams and equations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.20,0:13:22.65,Punchline-Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and instructions on what \Nto do on certain dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.65,0:13:25.67,Punchline-Flashback,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I was sending them to someone by fax.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.06,0:13:28.73,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Miyaken,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.13,0:13:40.75,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.12,0:13:42.46,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.46,0:13:45.47,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,You broke Tomoda's arms and legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.87,0:13:48.03,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Chiranosuke's Code, number one...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.03,0:13:51.67,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I must not change history \Nwithout your permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.67,0:13:52.97,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,If you know, then why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.97,0:13:54.81,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What was I supposed to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.81,0:13:58.10,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't just let Tomoda walk away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.50,0:14:03.48,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,If things went like the last time, \Nhe'd have killed two of Ito's classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.94,0:14:06.78,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,All for just two people?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.78,0:14:11.12,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Two people who did horrible \Nthings to Ito, no less.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.12,0:14:14.70,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't mean I can let them die!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:19.70,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,A little sacrifice is inevitable \Nto save seven billion lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.60,0:14:24.07,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.07,0:14:25.65,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Does it matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.98,0:14:35.33,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,That said, I don't actually \Nknow where I should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.08,0:14:38.44,Punchline-Flashback,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,He was given to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.78,0:14:41.77,Punchline-Flashback,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,From Rabura's little brother, Rando-oniichan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.77,0:14:44.67,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I should go ask that Rando guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.23,0:14:49.37,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ito, there's something I want to ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.48,0:14:52.08,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.58,0:14:56.72,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Is she out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.56,0:14:59.61,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.70,0:15:03.63,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.81,0:15:08.51,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, I'll get you free.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.58,0:15:14.26,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,It's so cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.77,0:15:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Panties!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.31,0:15:24.90,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,You pervert!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.15,0:15:31.44,Punchline-Soul,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Soul
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.73,0:15:29.56,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, you're misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.56,0:15:31.45,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,What am I misunderstanding, you pervert?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.45,0:15:33.67,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a pervert.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.67,0:15:35.46,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, he's a perbeart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.18,0:15:38.06,Punchline-Pervert,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Pervert
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.46,0:15:37.13,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,It's the perbeart's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.60,0:15:38.06,Punchline-Pervert2 - Copy,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Perbeart
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.13,0:15:38.23,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,Perbeart?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.23,0:15:42.15,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Muhi was acting weird, making \Na racket under the kotatsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.48,0:15:43.71,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,So I looked inside, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.04,0:15:46.46,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about Muhi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.46,0:15:47.62,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.62,0:15:49.19,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Rabura.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.19,0:15:50.48,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,From Rabura?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.90,0:15:53.43,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,She's so loose-lipped, \Nit's like she's leaking helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.43,0:15:55.91,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,She'll flap her gums about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.70,0:16:02.35,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, speaking of Rabura, \Ndo you know where her brother is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.35,0:16:03.85,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,Where's this coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.85,0:16:06.61,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Just tell me. You're cousins, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.08,0:16:09.11,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,We are, but why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.11,0:16:11.36,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I have business with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:13.97,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,Just ask Rabura, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.97,0:16:16.08,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think she'd tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.39,0:16:19.11,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,She's so tight-lipped, it's like trying \Nto shove barium down her throat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.11,0:16:21.12,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,You just said helium a minute ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.12,0:16:23.07,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the point!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.07,0:16:26.63,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,Rando-oniichan is coming here this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.63,0:16:27.33,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.86,0:16:29.88,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,He wants to check on Muhi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.88,0:16:32.37,Punchline-Soul,,0000,0000,0000,,Soul
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.33,0:16:37.39,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So you know about the Qmay Group's plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.82,0:16:39.92,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there's no point in hiding it, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.35,0:16:43.00,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,I used to be a Qmay Group devotee.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.54,0:16:44.90,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,A fervent one, at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.53,0:16:47.76,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,Tsubouchi Qmay took a liking to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.80,0:16:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he put me in charge of caring for Muhi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.98,0:16:55.68,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,I was ordered to take him from \Na research facility deep in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.68,0:16:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the mountains of Nagano \Nto the Tokyo headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.84,0:17:01.16,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,But I ended up going...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.16,0:17:02.42,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,To Korai House.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.84,0:17:04.81,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,You came to give Muhi to Ito.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.49,0:17:09.85,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you defy your orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.85,0:17:12.30,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,To stop the project, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.84,0:17:15.80,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,Without Muhi, they can't make W.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.80,0:17:18.80,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,But you said you were a fervent devotee.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.75,0:17:24.17,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,You know how they say that the day\Nbefore the field trip is the most fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.97,0:17:29.06,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,I was intoxicated by the Qmay Group's \Nteachings because they were so unrealistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.85,0:17:32.28,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,Then it became real, and I got turned off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.05,0:17:37.07,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do after you gave Muhi to Ito?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.55,0:17:41.39,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,I headed back to the mountains in \Nmy car, and ran into a guard rail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.36,0:17:45.37,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,In order to make it look like \NMuhi got away in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.04,0:17:47.83,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,That's how you got injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.83,0:17:50.71,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,No, this isn't from the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.28,0:17:53.46,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,The Qmay Group people did it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.84,0:17:56.29,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,As punishment for letting Muhi get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.99,0:17:59.47,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I came to quit the group.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.98,0:18:04.35,Default,Rando,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-chan covered the expensive resignation fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.00,0:18:16.72,Punchline-Song_Credits,Text,0000,0000,0000,,"Tsugaru Forced-Sightseeing"\NLyrics: Uchikoshi Koutarou \NMusic: Komuro Tetsuya
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.12,0:18:18.74,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,The apples of Tsugaru are ripe with nectar...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.74,0:18:23.74,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,Even Dracula eats the garlic grown in Tsugaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.02,0:18:29.25,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, by the way, is it true that Meika \Nis Strange Juice's right-hand man?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.62,0:18:31.81,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Code name: Pumpkin Chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.81,0:18:34.63,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,I'm basically in charge of mechanical engineering.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.63,0:18:37.13,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,Then you made that costume, Meika?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.13,0:18:38.29,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.64,0:18:41.11,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, Narugino, you're going on
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.11,0:18:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,missions without wearing your \Nshort pants, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.34,0:18:45.39,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,The size isn't quite right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.67,0:18:47.98,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,They are pretty tight, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.26,0:18:50.93,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,It'll fine. I'll lose weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.19,0:18:53.77,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,You totally won't, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.13,0:18:57.77,Punchline-Song_Credits,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(667,1)}Harakiri Harrassment \NLyrics: Uchikoshi Koutarou \NMusic: Komuro Tetsuya
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.98,0:19:01.49,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Eager harakiri...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.49,0:19:05.20,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Heart-pounding, gut-wrenching...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.20,0:19:08.96,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Eager harakiri...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.83,0:19:19.13,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Yuta-kun, you're up next.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.13,0:19:21.39,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? No, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.62,0:19:23.14,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,You're not getting out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.14,0:19:24.29,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,It's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.29,0:19:25.93,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,It's your duty as a resident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.93,0:19:27.66,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't want to!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.66,0:19:28.98,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.35,0:19:32.68,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,No! I'm not singing, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.68,0:19:34.19,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what anyone says—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.19,0:19:38.40,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,So white and plump...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.40,0:19:42.42,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I want to stack your buns
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.42,0:19:49.00,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,higher than Burj Khalifa!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.02,0:19:51.52,Punchline-Song_Credits,Text,0000,0000,0000,,I Wanna Stack Your Buns \NLyrics: Uchikoshi Koutarou\NMusic: Komuro Tetsuya
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.62,0:19:55.00,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Korai House is the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.00,0:19:56.50,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.56,0:20:01.47,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Rabura-san, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.03,0:20:09.48,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, when should we do this next?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.48,0:20:10.89,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,A party?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.89,0:20:13.90,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,The closest celebration is New Year's Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.90,0:20:15.98,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,That's a bit soon, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.31,0:20:19.15,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,We can do something else, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.15,0:20:23.21,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Like, an event that will\Nget our hearts pumping...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.21,0:20:24.37,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Like...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.72,0:20:25.77,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Fireworks?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.49,0:20:27.58,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Fireworks?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.89,0:20:29.08,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.42,0:20:31.68,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Fireworks in the middle of winter...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.68,0:20:34.21,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I just love the mismatch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.02,0:20:39.92,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's all do \Nfireworks on New Year's Eve!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.92,0:20:42.59,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Woo-hoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.08,0:20:48.18,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What did you want to talk to me about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.68,0:20:52.25,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I wanted to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.25,0:20:53.19,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Thank me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.76,0:20:57.12,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,You helped me when the \Nbus hijacking happened, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.53,0:20:58.69,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.18,0:21:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.23,0:21:05.45,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to thank me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.99,0:21:11.55,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I've felt since I first met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.33,0:21:15.56,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,You give me a really nostalgic feeling, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.56,0:21:22.21,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, that was a weird thing to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.90,0:21:23.89,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.07,0:21:29.35,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Narugino!
